<div class="modal fade" id="search-help-modal" role="dialog">
    <div class="modal-dialog">
        <div class="modal-content" style="width: 400px;">
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div class="search-help-filters-div"> 
                    <p style="font-size: 20px; text-decoration: underline;"><b>Tip:</b></p>
                    <p><strong>Combining searches: </strong>Use <b>&</b> or <b>,</b> to combine searches as an and statement. For example, searching for grass&kanto will show all Kanto Grass-type Pokémon.</p>
                              
                    <p style="font-size: 20px; text-decoration: underline;"><b>Filters:</b></p>
                    <p><strong>Pokédex number: </strong>Search by number to show all the Pokémon matching that Pokédex number. For example, searching for 25 will show all the Pikachu in your list.</p>
                    <p><strong>Name: </strong>Search by the Pokémon name. For example, searching Pikachu will show all the Pikachu in your Pokémon list.</p>
                    <p><strong>Region: </strong>Search Kanto, Johto, Hoenn, Sinnoh, Unova, or Galar to show all Pokémon from that region.</p>
                    <p><strong>Form: </strong>Add <b>%</b> before alola or galar to to show any Alolan or Galar Pokémon in your list</p>
                    <p><strong>Event: </strong>Add <b>?</b> before a name of an event. For example, searching %communityday will show all Pokémon that featured in a Community Day.</p>
                    <p><strong>Keywords: </strong>Search by some keywords like <b>costume</b>, 
                        <b>regional</b>, <b>shadow</b>, <b>purified</b>, <b>exclusive</b>, <b>tradable</b>, 
                        <b>deployable</b>, <b>transferable</b>, <b>evolve</b>, <b>tradeevolve</b>, <b>itemevolve</b>, 
                        <b>baby</b>, <b>legendary</b>, <b>mythical</b>, <b>starter</b>, <b>fossil</b>, <b>pseudo-legendary</b>, <b>ultrabeast</b></p>
                    <p><strong>Generation: </strong>Add <b>gen</b> before the number of a generation to show all Pokémon of that generation.</p>
                    <p><strong>Have/!Have: </strong>Search <b>have</b> to show all Pokémon that you have at least one shiny. The opposite <b>!have</b> search will show the list of Pokémon that you don't have. </p>
                    <p><strong>Pokémon Type: </strong>Enter a Pokémon type to show all Pokemon that match that type. For example, searching for grass will show all grass-type Pokémon in your list.</p>
                    <p><strong>Evolutionary family: </strong> Add <b>+</b> before a Pokémon’s name. For example, searching for +Pikachu will show any Pichu, Pikachu, and Raichu in your list.</p>
                    <p><strong>Evolutionary family (with Pokédex number): </strong> Add <b>+</b> before a Pokémon’s Pokédex number. For example, searching for +25 will show any Pichu, Pikachu, and Raichu in your list.</p>
                    <p><strong>Pokédex number range: </strong>Type <b>-10</b> to find all your Pokémon with Pokédex number equal to or less than 10 
                        or type <b>10-</b> to find all your Pokémon with Pokédex number equal to or higher than 10. 
                        You can also type <b>10-20</b>> to find all your Pokémon with Pokédex number between 10 and 20.</p>
                    <p><strong>Quantity: </strong>Type <b>quantity5</b> to find all Pokémon that you have 2 shiny. Also you can type <b>quantity-5</b> to find the Pokémon that you have less or equal than 5 
                        shiny or type <b>quantity5-</b> to find the Pokémon that you have at least 5 shiny. 
                        You can also type <b>quantity5-7</b> to find the Pokémon that you have between 5 and 7 shiny.</p>
                    <p><strong>Year: </strong>Search year plus a number to show Shiny Pokémon released in a given year. For example, <b>year2020</b> will show all Shiny Pokémon released in 2020.</p>
                    

                    </div>
                
